# Forge holds no model provider key of its own — users bring their own
# credentials through the in-app Providers panel, and each is stored in an
# httpOnly cookie, never in the environment:
#   - a Hugging Face token for cloud chat
#   - an OpenAI-compatible connection for chat against your own provider
#   - an OpenAI-compatible connection for codegen (the AI that writes playgrounds)
#
# The one OPTIONAL server var below is the shared codegen on-ramp.

# Optional. A Groq API key used as the SHARED DEFAULT for playground codegen, so
# new users can generate playgrounds with zero setup. A user's own codegen
# connection (set in the Providers panel) always takes precedence over this — a
# depleted user key never falls back to yours. Leave unset to require every user
# to bring their own codegen provider (e.g. for a self-hosted instance).
# Get one at https://console.groq.com/keys
GROQ_API_KEY=
